definitions: a period or act of preparation for a game, performance, or exercise session, involving gentle exercise or practice
shortDefinitions: period or act of preparation for match, performance, or exercise session

definitions: a garment worn during light exercise or training; a sweatsuit

examples.text: he took off his warm-ups and started shaking his muscles

shortDefinitions: garment worn during light exercise or training

definitions: a period before a stage performance in which the audience is amused or entertained in order to make it more receptive to the main act
shortDefinitions: period before stage performance in which audience is entertained
